# 🏗️ Basic PC Components

## CPU (Central Processing Unit)

### Kya Hai?

CPU computer ka **brain** hota hai.

Ye saare calculations perform karta hai aur instructions execute karta hai.

### Real World Analogy 🧠

Socho CPU office ka manager hai.

- Kis employee ko kya kaam karna hai
- Kaunsi file pehle process hogi
- Kaunsa task important hai

Sab decisions CPU leta hai.

### Mere System Mein

```text
Intel Core i7-13650HX
14 Cores
20 Logical Processors
```

---

## RAM (Random Access Memory)

### Kya Hai?

RAM temporary working memory hoti hai.

Jitne applications open honge, utni RAM use hogi.

### Real World Analogy 📚

Socho tumhari study table.

- Badi table = Zyada books ek saath khol sakte ho
- Chhoti table = Baar-baar books replace karni padengi

RAM bhi waise hi kaam karti hai.

### Mere System Mein

```text
Installed RAM: 16 GB
```

---

## SSD (Solid State Drive)

### Kya Hai?

SSD permanent storage device hai.

Isme:

- Windows install hota hai
- Software install hote hain
- Files store hoti hain

### Real World Analogy 🗄️

Socho ek locker.

Jab computer band ho jata hai tab bhi data locker me safe rehta hai.

SSD bhi waise hi data save rakhta hai.

---

## Motherboard

### Kya Hai?

Motherboard computer ka main circuit board hota hai.

Saare hardware isi se connected hote hain.

### Connected Components

- CPU
- RAM
- SSD
- GPU
- USB Ports
- Network Adapter

### Real World Analogy 🏙️

Socho ek city.

Motherboard us city ki roads aur infrastructure hai.

Saare components isi ke through communicate karte hain.

---

## PSU (Power Supply Unit)

### Kya Hai?

PSU wall electricity ko computer ke usable voltage me convert karta hai.

### Real World Analogy ⚡

Power Station → Electricity

PSU → Computer ko safe power supply

---

# 🛠️ System Information Tool

# 1️⃣ msinfo32

## Purpose

System ki complete hardware aur software information dikhata hai.

## Command

```cmd
msinfo32
```

## Information Available

- Windows Version
- System Model
- BIOS Version
- CPU
- RAM
- Motherboard
- Drivers
- Security Features

---

## Real World Analogy 📖

Socho hospital ki patient file.

Usme patient ki poori history likhi hoti hai.

`msinfo32` computer ki waise hi complete history file hai.

---

## Service Desk Use

User pooche:

> Mera laptop model kya hai?

> Mere system me kitni RAM hai?

> BIOS version kya hai?

Answer:

```cmd
msinfo32
```

---

# 2️⃣ CPU Information

## Command

```cmd
wmic cpu get name
```

## Purpose

Processor ka exact model name dikhata hai.

---

## Breakdown

| Command Part | Meaning |
|--------------|----------|
| wmic | Windows Management Instrumentation |
| cpu | CPU Information |
| get name | Processor Name Show Karo |

---

## Example Output

```text
Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-13650HX
```

---

## Real World Analogy 🚗

Car ka bonnet khole bina engine model dekhna.

Waise hi:

```cmd
wmic cpu get name
```

Laptop khole bina CPU model bata deta hai.

---

## Service Desk Use

Compatibility Check

Example:

- VMware
- VirtualBox
- Android Studio
- Video Editing Software

CPU model dekhkar hardware capability verify kar sakte hain.

---

# 3️⃣ RAM Information

## Command

```cmd
wmic memorychip get capacity
```

## Purpose

Har RAM stick ki capacity dikhata hai.

---

## Example Output

```text
8589934592
8589934592
```

### Conversion

```text
8589934592 Bytes = 8 GB
```

Result:

```text
8 GB + 8 GB = 16 GB
```

---

## Real World Analogy 📚

Almirah me kitni shelves hain aur har shelf me kitni books aa sakti hain.

Ye command har RAM module ki capacity batati hai.

---

## Service Desk Use

RAM Upgrade Planning

Example:

Current:

```text
8 GB + 8 GB
```

Upgrade:

```text
16 GB + 16 GB = 32 GB
```

---

# 4️⃣ Disk Information

## Command

```cmd
wmic diskdrive get model,size,mediatype
```

## Purpose

Storage device ki details dikhata hai.

---

## Information Available

- Disk Model
- Disk Size
- Media Type

---

## Example Output

```text
Samsung SSD 512GB
```

---

## Real World Analogy 🗄️

Warehouse inventory card.

Batata hai:

- Kaunsi storage lagi hai
- Kitni capacity hai
- Kis type ki hai

---

## Service Desk Use

User:

> System slow chal raha hai.

Check:

```cmd
wmic diskdrive get model,size,mediatype
```

Identify:

- HDD
- SATA SSD
- NVMe SSD

---

# 5️⃣ Total Physical Memory

## Command

```cmd
systeminfo | findstr /C:"Total Physical Memory"
```

---

## Purpose

System ki total installed RAM quickly dikhata hai.

---

## Breakdown

### systeminfo

Complete system report generate karta hai.

---

### Pipe ( | )

Ek command ka output dusri command ko pass karta hai.

```text
systeminfo
      ↓
      |
      ↓
findstr
```

---

### findstr

Specific text search karta hai.

```cmd
findstr /C:"Total Physical Memory"
```

Sirf RAM wali line dikhata hai.

---

## Example Output

```text
Total Physical Memory: 15,874 MB
```

---

## Service Desk Use

Quick RAM Verification

Remote troubleshooting me useful.

